standard_text: [INDEMNIFYING_PARTY] shall defend, indemnify, and hold harmless [INDEMNIFIED_PARTY] and its officers, directors, employees, agents, successors, and assigns (collectively, "Indemnitees") from and against any and all claims, demands, suits, actions, proceedings, losses, damages, liabilities, settlements, costs, and expenses (including reasonable attorneys' fees and court costs) (collectively, "Claims") arising out of or relating to: (a) any breach or alleged breach of [INDEMNIFYING_PARTY]'s representations, warranties, or obligations under this Agreement; (b) any negligent or willful acts or omissions of [INDEMNIFYING_PARTY] or its employees, agents, or contractors; (c) any infringement or alleged infringement of any intellectual property rights, including patents, copyrights, trademarks, or trade secrets; (d) any violation of applicable laws, regulations, or industry standards by [INDEMNIFYING_PARTY]; (e) any bodily injury, death, or property damage caused by [INDEMNIFYING_PARTY]'s performance under this Agreement; or (f) any claims by third parties arising from [INDEMNIFYING_PARTY]'s services, products, or deliverables. [INDEMNIFYING_PARTY]'s obligations hereunder include the duty to defend against such Claims using counsel reasonably acceptable to [INDEMNIFIED_PARTY], and to pay all resulting judgments, settlements, damages, and costs. [INDEMNIFIED_PARTY] shall provide prompt written notice of any Claim, cooperate reasonably in the defense, and may participate in the defense with its own counsel at its own expense. [INDEMNIFYING_PARTY] shall not settle any Claim without [INDEMNIFIED_PARTY]'s prior written consent, which shall not be unreasonably withheld. These indemnification obligations shall survive termination of this Agreement.

standard_text: Influencer agrees to comply with all applicable FTC guidelines and shall include appropriate disclosure language (e.g., #ad, #sponsored) in all content created under this Agreement.
[PARTY B] shall return all Confidential Information in [PARTY B]'s possession within one (1) business day of termination or expiration of the Agreement and retain no copies.
plain_english_summary: Talent must return all confidential materials immediately after termination.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall direct all press inquiries related to services under the Agreement to [PARTY A] and shall not communicate with the press without [PARTY A]'s prior written approval.
plain_english_summary: Talent must not speak to press without written approval from the brand.

standard_text: If [PARTY B] perishes or suffers any disability preventing the performance of Services for more than thirty (30) days, [PARTY A] may terminate the Agreement.
plain_english_summary: Brand may terminate if Talent dies or is disabled for over 30 days.

standard_text: If an Event of Force Majeure occurs and continues for more than fifteen (15) days, [PARTY A] may terminate the Agreement.
plain_english_summary: Brand may terminate if force majeure lasts more than 15 days.

standard_text: Upon termination under disability or force majeure provisions, [PARTY B] is only entitled to compensation accrued as of the date of termination and must promptly refund any unearned amounts.
plain_english_summary: Talent receives only earned compensation and must refund the rest upon certain terminations.

standard_text: If [PARTY B] fails to post any agreed Services on any agreed Production Day for reasons other than a Force Majeure Event, the Agreement shall be considered null and void, and [PARTY A] shall owe no amounts.
plain_english_summary: Failing to post on time voids the contract and Talent is not owed payment.

standard_text: A Force Majeure Event includes natural catastrophes, labor disputes, acts of God, war, carrier delays, disease, outbreak, governmental orders, or any similar cause beyond [PARTY B]'s control that affects Services or [PARTY A]'s rights.
plain_english_summary: Defines force majeure conditions that excuse Talent's duties.

standard_text: [PARTY A] may immediately terminate the Agreement if [PARTY B] commits any act that is an offense under applicable law, brings [PARTY B] or [PARTY A] into public disrepute, scandal, ridicule, or harms any of [PARTY A]'s products.
plain_english_summary: Brand may immediately terminate for morals violations or reputational harm.

standard_text: [PARTY A] may immediately terminate if [PARTY B] materially breaches any provision or representation of the Agreement.
plain_english_summary: Material breach allows immediate termination.

standard_text: [PARTY A] may immediately terminate if [PARTY B] makes any statement that defames or disparages [PARTY A] or its products privately or publicly.
plain_english_summary: Defamation or disparagement triggers immediate termination.

standard_text: If [PARTY A] terminates under the morals or breach provisions, [PARTY A] shall only pay [PARTY B] for Services actually rendered up to termination, and [PARTY B] must promptly refund any unearned compensation.
plain_english_summary: Termination for cause results in pro rata pay and refunds of unearned amounts.

standard_text: During the Term of this Agreement and for a period of [EXCLUSIVITY_MONTHS] months following the completion of the final Deliverable (the "Exclusivity Period"), [CREATOR_NAME] agrees not to create, post, publish, or otherwise promote any content on behalf of any brand, company, product, or service that competes with [BRAND_NAME] in the [CATEGORY] category (a "Competing Brand"). For purposes of this Agreement, a Competing Brand shall be defined as any entity that manufactures, distributes, markets, or sells [PRODUCT_TYPE] or services that are substantially similar to or directly competitive with [BRAND_NAME]'s offerings, as reasonably determined by [BRAND_NAME]. This exclusivity restriction applies to all platforms, channels, and media, including but not limited to social media posts, stories, videos, blog content, podcast appearances, speaking engagements, and any other form of content creation or endorsement. Notwithstanding the foregoing, this exclusivity clause shall not prohibit [CREATOR_NAME] from: (i) using or personally consuming competing products for their own non-commercial purposes; (ii) creating content about competing products that is purely educational, journalistic, or review-based in nature and is not sponsored or compensated by the competing brand; or (iii) fulfilling contractual obligations to Competing Brands that were entered into prior to the Effective Date of this Agreement, provided that [CREATOR_NAME] disclosed such pre-existing relationships to [BRAND_NAME] in writing prior to execution of this Agreement. In consideration for this exclusivity commitment, [BRAND_NAME] agrees to pay [CREATOR_NAME] the Exclusivity Fee as specified in Section [X], which shall be in addition to the base compensation for Deliverables.

standard_text: All invoices submitted by Contractor shall be paid by [PARTY_NAME] within [NET_DAYS] days of the invoice date (the "Payment Period"). Invoices must include detailed descriptions of services rendered, applicable dates, and any supporting documentation as reasonably requested by Client. Payment shall be made via wire transfer, ACH, or other mutually agreed payment method to the account designated by Contractor in writing. In the event payment is not received within the Payment Period, the outstanding amount shall accrue interest at a rate of [PERCENTAGE]% per month (or [PERCENTAGE]% per annum) or the maximum rate permitted by applicable law, whichever is less. Late payments exceeding [NET_DAYS] days shall entitle Contractor to suspend performance of Services until all outstanding amounts are paid in full, without waiving Contractor's right to terminate this Agreement for material breach. [PARTY_NAME] shall be responsible for all reasonable costs of collection, including but not limited to attorney fees, court costs, and collection agency fees incurred in collecting any overdue amounts. For avoidance of doubt, disputes regarding specific invoice line items shall not excuse payment of undisputed amounts. Contractor shall provide all required tax documentation, including Form W-9 or W-8BEN as applicable, prior to processing of first payment.

standard_text: Influencer hereby grants to Dior a worldwide, exclusive, sublicensable license to use, reproduce, distribute and display the Social Media Content during the usage term in the forms of media specified in the agreement's usage section.
plain_english_summary: Gives Dior an exclusive worldwide sublicensable license to the Social Media Content during the agreed usage term.

standard_text: Any Social Media Content posted or displayed by Dior or its retail partners during the usage term does not need to be removed at the end of the usage period, and Dior may use the Social Media Content during and following the usage term for internal and archival purposes.
plain_english_summary: Allows Dior and its retail partners to keep using the Social Media Content for internal and archival purposes even after the usage term ends.

standard_text: Influencer shall not use the name or trademarks of Dior or any of its affiliates except as incorporated into the Social Media Content and approved by Dior in each instance, such approval applying only to the specific purpose and instance of use, and Influencer agrees that it has no right, title or interest in Dior IP and shall not acquire any rights in Dior IP through use.
plain_english_summary: Restricts Influencer's use of Dior brands and confirms that all goodwill and rights in Dior IP remain with Dior.

standard_text: [PARTY A]'s decision to terminate under the morals clause must be exercised within forty-five (45) days after the facts giving rise to such right are brought to [PARTY A]'s attention.
plain_english_summary: Brand must act within 45 days to terminate for morals clause triggers.

standard_text: "Content" or "Deliverables" means all photographs, videos, posts, stories, and other materials created by Influencer pursuant to this Agreement.
plain_english_summary: Defines what constitutes deliverable content.

standard_text: "Products" means the Company's products, including but not limited to [PRODUCT CATEGORY], that are the subject of this Agreement.
plain_english_summary: Defines the products being promoted.

standard_text: "Social Platforms" means Instagram, TikTok, YouTube, and any other social media platforms specified in the Statement of Work.
plain_english_summary: Defines which social media platforms are covered.

standard_text: All content created under this Agreement must be submitted to the Brand for review and approval prior to publication. The Brand shall provide feedback within three (3) business days of receipt.
Payment shall be made within thirty (30) days of receipt of invoice and upon Brand's approval of all deliverables. Influencer shall submit invoice upon completion of services.

Each party retains all right, title and interest in its own intellectual property, including trademarks and copyrights, and all renewals, extensions, revivals and resuscitations thereof, throughout the universe in perpetuity in all media now known or hereafter devised.
plain_english_summary: Confirms that each party keeps ownership of its own intellectual property and associated rights in all media and territories.

standard_text: The Territory for the campaign and all Services provided by [PARTY B] shall be limited to the United Kingdom.
plain_english_summary: Defines the campaign territory as the UK.

standard_text: [PARTY A] shall pay [PARTY B] a Fee of [AMOUNT], with one hundred percent (100%) payable upon content approval, on fourteen (14) day payment terms.
plain_english_summary: Fee due entirely upon approval, payable within 14 days.

standard_text: Any late payments shall incur a late payment charge.
plain_english_summary: Late fees apply to overdue payments.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall deliver one (1) Instagram post and one (1) Instagram Story set of three (3) frames on the specified accounts, in accordance with the Brief.
plain_english_summary: Defines the required deliverables for Instagram.

standard_text: All content must be submitted to [PARTY A] for approval before posting.
plain_english_summary: Content must be pre-approved by the client.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall not promote any competitor brands for seven (7) days after the content goes live.
plain_english_summary: 7-day competitor blackout period.

standard_text: The content is owned by [PARTY B]. [PARTY A] may re-post or re-gram such content provided they tag or reference [PARTY B].
plain_english_summary: Client may re-share content but must tag the Talent; Talent retains ownership.

standard_text: Notice of material breach must be provided in writing, specifying the nature of the breach and the requirement to remedy it within fourteen (14) calendar days (excluding weekends and UK public holidays).
plain_english_summary: Defines breach notice and cure-period rules.

standard_text: Either party may terminate immediately if the other party materially breaches the Agreement and fails to remedy within the cure period.
plain_english_summary: Allows immediate termination for uncured material breach.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall comply with all applicable UK advertising regulations including ASA guidelines on social media promotions.
plain_english_summary: Talent must comply with ASA and UK advertising laws.

standard_text: All correspondence relating to Services must be directed through the Agency and not directly between [PARTY A] and [PARTY B], unless authorised.
plain_english_summary: Client cannot contact Talent directly unless allowed.

standard_text: The Social Media Posts and Images shall remain the property of [PARTY B] for the full copyright period and any possible extensions.
plain_english_summary: Confirms Talent owns full copyright over content.

standard_text: The Agreement and any dispute arising from it is governed by the laws of England and Wales, with exclusive jurisdiction of the English courts.
plain_english_summary: Governing law and court jurisdiction set to England and Wales.

standard_text: This Agreement is not binding unless signed by Influencer Matchmaker Ltd and contains the full understanding of the parties.
plain_english_summary: Defines validity requirement and full-agreement clause.

standard_text: "Confidential Information" means any non-public information disclosed by either Party, including business plans, marketing strategies, product information, and financial data.
plain_english_summary: Defines what information is considered confidential.

standard_text: All Confidential Information, including copies, files, and documents, shall remain the exclusive property of [PARTY A].
plain_english_summary: Brand retains ownership of all confidential materials.

standard_text: Dior shall have the right to use the Social Media Content for six months following the date the Social Media Content goes live in Dior digital platforms, including Dior.com and Dior social media channels, and on Dior's retail partners' digital platforms and social media channels, on an organic basis only, with any paid use during the usage term subject to the parties' agreement on an additional fee of [AMOUNT] per thirty days.
plain_english_summary: Grants Dior time limited organic usage rights over the Social Media Content on its own and retailer platforms, and requires an additional fee for any paid promotion during that period.

standard_text: Influencer shall post the Social Media Content on mutually agreed dates and must provide drafts of all Social Media Content for Dior's review and edit no less than five business days before the scheduled go live date.
plain_english_summary: Sets timelines for agreeing posting dates and requires draft content to be provided at least five business days before going live.

standard_text: Influencer agrees to perform the services described in the agreement in a professional and workmanlike manner, consistent with the degree of care and skill ordinarily exercised under similar circumstances in the industry, and consistent with the schedule on the cover page and any applicable guidelines unless otherwise mutually agreed in writing.
plain_english_summary: Requires Influencer to perform the services to industry professional standards and in line with the agreed schedule and guidelines.

standard_text: Once posted, Social Media Content shall remain on Influencer's applicable social media channel for at least twelve months following the go live date, provided that Instagram stories and similar ephemeral content may expire in the ordinary course.
plain_english_summary: Requires Influencer to keep social posts live for at least twelve months, except for naturally expiring story type content.

standard_text: In consideration for Influencer's performance of the services, Dior shall pay Influencer a fee of [AMOUNT], payable in full to Influencer or Influencer's authorized representative upon completion of all services, against an invoice issued on completion, with payment due within thirty days of Dior's receipt of such invoice, by check or wire at Dior's discretion to the payee details provided in writing.
plain_english_summary: Sets out the base fee amount, that it is payable after all services are completed, and that Dior must pay within thirty days of receiving a proper invoice.

standard_text: Any paid use of the Social Media Content during the usage term, including sponsored posts, promotion or whitelisting, is subject to the parties' agreement on an additional fee of [AMOUNT] per thirty days of such paid use.
plain_english_summary: Provides for an additional monthly fee if Dior wishes to use the Social Media Content in paid media during the usage term.

standard_text: Either party may terminate this Agreement with thirty (30) days written notice. In case of material breach, the non-breaching party may terminate immediately upon written notice.
Influencer agrees to maintain the confidentiality of all proprietary information received from Brand and shall not disclose such information to third parties without prior written consent.
Brand shall have the right to use, reproduce, and distribute the content created under this Agreement for a period of one (1) year from the publication date across all digital platforms.

Except for references to Influencer's name expressly authorized in the agreement, Dior shall not use the name, image, likeness, voice, biographical data or trademarks of Influencer without Influencer's prior written approval in each instance, provided that this agreement constitutes Influencer's prior written approval for Dior to use the Influencer IP to the extent incorporated into the Social Media Content and used in a manner permitted by the agreement, and Dior acquires no rights in the Influencer IP beyond such permitted use.
plain_english_summary: Limits Dior's use of Influencer's personal brand and likeness to agreed uses within the Social Media Content and confirms that Influencer retains all rights in Influencer IP.

standard_text: Influencer shall create and post the Social Media Content consisting of one Instagram story of at least three frames including a link sticker on at least one frame, one Instagram reel with in feed preview, and one TikTok video plus a syndicated TikTok from the Instagram reel, on Influencer's channels, incorporating the specified tagged accounts, hashtags and brand provided links, to promote the campaign and subject to Dior's approval prior to posting.
plain_english_summary: Defines the specific social media deliverables, platforms, tagging, hashtags, links and approval requirement for the campaign.

standard_text: If Dior provides creative guidelines in advance of a scheduled posting date, Influencer will comply with those guidelines when preparing the Social Media Content, and may be required, at Dior's sole discretion, to reshoot or edit the Social Media Content if Influencer does not comply, and no Social Media Content shall be posted or otherwise shared publicly before Dior's written approval.
plain_english_summary: Obliges Influencer to follow Dior's creative guidelines, gives Dior the right to demand reshoots or edits for non compliance, and requires Dior's written approval before any content is posted.

standard_text: Influencer shall be solely responsible for all broker and agent fees or commissions, taxes, withholdings and other amounts due to third parties in connection with the agreement or the services, Dior shall have no liability for such amounts, and expenses incurred by Influencer are not reimbursable unless Dior expressly approves them in writing in advance and Influencer provides reasonably sufficient supporting documentation, in which case Dior will reimburse in accordance with its expense reimbursement policies.
plain_english_summary: Places responsibility on Influencer for all commissions, taxes and third party amounts, and makes expenses non reimbursable unless Dior pre approves them and they are properly documented.

standard_text: The term of the agreement commences on the effective date and ends on [DATE] unless earlier terminated in accordance with the agreement.
plain_english_summary: Sets the start and end dates of the agreement, subject to earlier termination rights.

standard_text: Either party may terminate the agreement upon prior written notice if the other party breaches the agreement and, if the breach is capable of cure, fails to cure it within fifteen days after receiving written notice of the breach.
plain_english_summary: Gives each party a right to terminate for uncured material breach after a fifteen day cure period where cure is possible.

standard_text: Dior may terminate the agreement upon prior written notice if Influencer commits an act or becomes involved in a situation that could result in conviction for a felony or for a misdemeanor involving a controlled substance or substance abuse, dies or suffers a disability preventing performance, becomes involved in a public scandal or makes public statements or engages in conduct shocking or offensive to a substantial community, or breaches the non disparagement obligations.
plain_english_summary: Gives Dior enhanced termination rights if Influencer is involved in crime, scandal, offensive conduct, inability to perform, or breaches the non disparagement clause.

standard_text: Any termination of the agreement under the termination section is without waiver of rights, and all rights and remedies are reserved notwithstanding such termination.
plain_english_summary: Clarifies that terminating the agreement does not waive any other rights or remedies a party may have.

standard_text: Any provisions of the terms and conditions that contemplate performance or observance after termination or expiration of the agreement will survive such termination or expiration and continue in full force and effect.
plain_english_summary: States that clauses intended to operate after termination continue to bind the parties.

standard_text: Content must align with Brand's creative guidelines and brand voice. Influencer shall incorporate provided key messages and maintain authentic tone consistent with their established content style.

[CREATOR_NAME] acknowledges and agrees that all content created pursuant to this Agreement constitutes a material connection between [CREATOR_NAME] and [BRAND_NAME] that must be disclosed to [CREATOR_NAME]'s audience in accordance with the Federal Trade Commission's Guides Concerning the Use of Endorsements and Testimonials in Advertising (16 C.F.R. Part 255) and any applicable state or international disclosure requirements. [CREATOR_NAME] shall include clear, conspicuous, and unambiguous disclosures in all Deliverables as follows: (i) for social media posts, the disclosure must appear above the "more" or "read more" break and shall use hashtags such as #ad, #sponsored, #[BRAND_NAME]partner, or other FTC-compliant disclosure language as approved by [BRAND_NAME]; (ii) for video content, the disclosure must appear both in the video title or description and verbally within the first thirty (30) seconds of the video using language such as "This video is sponsored by [BRAND_NAME]" or "I partnered with [BRAND_NAME] for this content"; (iii) for stories or ephemeral content, the disclosure must be included in each individual story segment, either as text overlay or using the platform's built-in "Paid Partnership" tag; and (iv) for any other content format, the disclosure must be placed in a location where it is easily noticeable by the average consumer and cannot be overlooked. [CREATOR_NAME] represents and warrants that all disclosures shall comply with the FTC's requirement that they be clear and conspicuous, meaning they must be difficult to miss, easy to understand, and in close proximity to the relevant claim. [BRAND_NAME] shall have the right to review and approve all disclosure language prior to publication to ensure compliance. Both parties acknowledge that failure to comply with FTC disclosure requirements may result in significant penalties, enforcement actions, and reputational harm, and [CREATOR_NAME] agrees to indemnify [BRAND_NAME] for any violations arising from [CREATOR_NAME]'s failure to disclose in accordance with this Section.

standard_text: Influencer further represents and warrants that the services will not be performed within the jurisdiction of any union or guild or under any union or guild agreement, that any claims made in the Social Media Content about Dior or its products will reflect Influencer's honest and truthful opinions, and that the Social Media Content does not violate any third party rights, including intellectual property rights.
plain_english_summary: Adds Influencer specific warranties that work is non union, that endorsements are truthful, and that the content will not infringe third party rights.

standard_text: Influencer agrees to comply with all applicable laws, regulations, rules and guidance with respect to the services, including the Federal Trade Commission Revised Endorsement and Testimonial Guidelines and any other FTC guidance then in effect, as well as any related guidelines provided by Dior, and to clearly and conspicuously disclose the relationship between Influencer and Dior in all Social Media Content using required disclosure language such as "#sponsored", "#ad" or "#paid ad" toward the beginning of the content.
plain_english_summary: Obliges Influencer to follow FTC endorsement rules and Dior's guidelines and to include clear paid partnership disclosures in all relevant posts.

standard_text: Neither party shall be liable or deemed in breach for any failure or delay in performing under the agreement to the extent caused by an event of force majeure, including acts of God, natural disaster, war, epidemic, pandemic, government order, law or action, national emergency or other similar events beyond the party's reasonable control, and in such case the parties shall negotiate in good faith appropriate modifications to the agreement, which may include extending the term or providing replacement services.
plain_english_summary: Excuses performance delays caused by specified force majeure events and requires the parties to negotiate good faith adjustments such as extensions or replacement services.

standard_text: Influencer is an independent contractor of Dior and not an employee, and the agreement does not create any association, joint venture, agency relationship or partnership between the parties, and neither party has authority to enter into agreements for, act as agent or representative of, or otherwise bind the other party.
plain_english_summary: Clarifies that Influencer is an independent contractor, not an employee or agent, and that neither party can bind the other.

standard_text: If Influencer enters into the agreement through a loan out entity, that loan out entity represents and warrants that it has full power and authority to enter into the agreement on Influencer's behalf and to bind Influencer, and covenants to cause Influencer to satisfy all of Influencer's obligations under the agreement and to be responsible for any breach or failure to perform by Influencer.
plain_english_summary: Extends responsibility to any loan out entity, requiring it to bind and ensure Influencer's performance and making it responsible for any breach.

standard_text: Influencer acknowledges that Dior does not provide or carry any insurance for the benefit of Influencer, and that Influencer is solely responsible for obtaining any and all insurance related to Influencer's performance of the services.
plain_english_summary: Requires Influencer to arrange their own insurance because Dior will not provide coverage for them.

standard_text: Influencer agrees to create and publish the following content: (1) One Instagram post, (2) One Instagram Story set (3-5 frames), (3) Three high-resolution images for Brand use.
Influencer agrees not to promote competing brands in the same product category for a period of ninety (90) days from the publication of content under this Agreement.

Dior agrees to indemnify, defend and hold Influencer and its successors and permitted assigns harmless from and against all claims arising out of or related to Dior's breach of its representations or warranties in the agreement, Dior's gross negligence or willful misconduct, or any actual or alleged product liability claims related to Dior's products.
plain_english_summary: Obligates Dior to indemnify Influencer for claims caused by Dior's breach, misconduct or product related liability.

standard_text: If any provision or clause of the agreement, or its application, is held invalid or unenforceable in any circumstance, such invalidity or unenforceability shall not affect the validity or enforceability of the remainder of the agreement or of the application of such provision or clause in any other circumstances.
plain_english_summary: Ensures that if one part of the agreement is invalid or unenforceable, the rest remains in effect.

standard_text: All notices, requests, demands and other correspondence under the agreement must be in writing and delivered by hand, e mail or nationally recognized private courier. Notices by hand or courier are deemed delivered when actually delivered, and notices by e mail are deemed delivered on the business day sent if sent before 5pm Eastern Time or on the next business day if sent at or after 5pm Eastern Time, provided no bounce back or error message is received. Notices must be sent to the addresses specified in the agreement or to any other address designated by notice under this section.
plain_english_summary: Sets formal requirements, delivery methods and deemed receipt times for notices between the parties.

standard_text: Influencer may not assign or transfer the agreement or any rights or obligations under it without Dior's prior written approval, and any attempted assignment or transfer not permitted is void from the outset.
plain_english_summary: Prohibits Influencer from assigning the agreement without Dior's written consent and makes unauthorized assignments void.

standard_text: The parties have jointly participated in negotiating and drafting the agreement and it shall be construed as if drafted jointly by them, with no presumption or burden of proof favoring or disfavoring any party based on authorship, and the words "including" and similar expressions mean "including without limitation", and unless the context requires otherwise, "neither", "nor", "any", "either" and "or" are not exclusive, references to sections, exhibits and schedules are to those of the agreement, and all words are to be construed by gender or number as circumstances require.
plain_english_summary: Sets interpretation rules, including no contra proferentem against the drafter and that "including" is non limiting and pronouns and references are read flexibly.

standard_text: The agreement may be executed by electronic transmission, including PDF or DocuSign, or by facsimile signature, and such signatures are binding, and the agreement may be executed in two or more counterparts, each of which constitutes an original and together form one agreement.
plain_english_summary: Recognizes electronic and facsimile signatures as valid and allows the agreement to be signed in multiple counterparts.

standard_text: Influencer agrees to indemnify and hold harmless the Brand from any claims arising from Influencer's breach of this Agreement or violation of any applicable laws.

Influencer agrees not to post any paid or sponsored content within the skincare category during the one day before or one day after the date on which any Social Media Content is posted by Influencer as part of the services.
plain_english_summary: Prevents Influencer from posting other paid or sponsored skincare content immediately before or after Dior campaign posts.

standard_text: At no time during or after the term of the agreement shall Influencer make any derogatory or disparaging statement regarding Dior, the products of Dior or its affiliates, LVMH Mot Hennessy Louis Vuitton SE, or any member of the Arnault family, or use Dior's name, the name of any officer, director, agent or employee of Dior or its affiliates, or any of Dior's trademarks or brand names, in a disparaging, derogatory or offensive manner.
plain_english_summary: Prohibits Influencer from making disparaging statements about Dior, its group, related parties or using their names and brands in a derogatory way at any time.

standard_text: Each party represents and warrants that it has the full right, power and authority to enter into and perform the agreement, that the agreement does not and will not conflict with or infringe upon any existing or future commitment of the party or the rights of any third party, and that it will comply with all applicable federal, state, local and other laws, rules and regulations in performing its obligations.
plain_english_summary: Provides mutual assurances about authority, absence of conflicting obligations, and compliance with applicable laws.

standard_text: Influencer may receive or have access to Dior's and its affiliates' non public proprietary business information, including the terms of the agreement, business, marketing and promotional plans, business plans, product and process information and other confidential information, which remains Dior's property, and Influencer agrees not to use such Confidential Information except to perform obligations under the agreement and not to disclose it during or after the term to any person or entity except as required by law or privately to attorneys, accountants, agents and other representatives who need to know and who keep it confidential.
plain_english_summary: Requires Influencer to keep Dior's confidential information, including the agreement terms and business information, secret and to use it only for performing the contract, with limited exceptions for legal requirements and professional advisers.

standard_text: Influencer agrees to indemnify, defend and hold Dior, its affiliates and their respective officers, directors, shareholders, members, employees, agents, successors and permitted assigns harmless from and against all third party claims, suits, judgments, losses, damages, penalties, fines and costs, including reasonable attorneys' fees and related expenses, arising out of or related to Influencer's breach of any representations, warranties or agreements in the agreement, Influencer's gross negligence or willful misconduct, or Influencer's performance of the services, including development, production or distribution of the Social Media Content by Influencer.
plain_english_summary: Requires Influencer to cover Dior for third party claims linked to Influencer's breach, misconduct or work on the Social Media Content, including legal fees.

standard_text: Influencer shall disclose affiliation with Company in all Influencer Content in a clear and conspicuous manner in accordance with the FTC Endorsement Guides.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must include clear FTC disclosures on all posts.

standard_text: Influencer shall include official links, tags, and required hashtags including #FentyBeautyPartner and tag @fentybeauty in each Influencer Content execution.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must include required tags and hashtags.

standard_text: Influencer shall submit analytics upon Company request in accordance with Company's schedule and guidelines.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must send analytics when requested.

standard_text: Influencer shall perform services using reasonable efforts, act in good faith, remain on approved key messages, and remove content upon Company request.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must follow messaging rules and remove content if asked.

standard_text: Influencer shall comply with all applicable laws and the FTC Endorsement Guides in connection with this Agreement.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must comply with FTC and legal requirements.

standard_text: Company shall pay Influencer a Fee of [AMOUNT], with 50% payable upon publication of the first two pieces of Influencer Content and 50% upon completion of all deliverables, Net 60.
plain_english_summary: Payment split into two installments, Net 60.

standard_text: Company shall not be liable for any broker, agent, production company, or third-party fees owed by Influencer.
plain_english_summary: Influencer is responsible for its own third-party fees.

standard_text: Influencer shall refund any prepaid unearned amounts if Company terminates for convenience.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must return unused prepaid funds.

standard_text: Any dispute, claim or controversy arising out of or relating to the agreement, including its breach, termination, enforcement, interpretation or validity and the scope or applicability of the agreement to arbitrate, shall be determined by final and binding arbitration in New York, New York before a single neutral arbitrator who is a retired U.S. federal judge, administered by JAMS under its Comprehensive Arbitration Rules as modified in the agreement, with the parties waiving all rights to trial by jury or court, applying New York substantive law without regard to conflicts principles, keeping all arbitration proceedings confidential, and allowing judgment on the award to be entered in any court with jurisdiction, with the arbitrator empowered to allocate arbitration costs and reasonable attorneys' fees to the losing party.
plain_english_summary: Requires confidential final and binding JAMS arbitration in New York under New York law for all disputes, with no jury or court trial and with costs and fees potentially awarded against the losing party.

standard_text: The agreement, including the cover page, terms and conditions and all exhibits, represents the entire understanding and agreement of the parties regarding its subject matter and supersedes all prior negotiations, understandings, representations or agreements between them, and each party waives any right to rely on such prior matters, and the agreement may not be amended or modified except by a written agreement executed by both parties, and in the event of conflict between the cover page and the terms and conditions, the cover page controls.
plain_english_summary: States that the written agreement is the complete and exclusive statement of the parties' arrangement, requires written signed amendments and gives priority to the cover page if there is inconsistency.

standard_text: Influencer shall create four TikTok videos syndicated to Reels during the Term, subject to Company approval, and reshoot up to two times at no extra fee if the brief is not followed.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must create four approved TikTok/Reels posts and reshoot if needed.

standard_text: Influencer Content shall not disparage Company or its competitors.
plain_english_summary: No negative statements about the Company or competitors.

standard_text: Company may terminate this Agreement for any reason with thirty (30) days prior written notice.
plain_english_summary: Company can terminate with 30 days notice.

standard_text: Company may immediately terminate if Influencer dies, suffers disability, fails to perform, or an Event of Force Majeure occurs.
plain_english_summary: Company may terminate immediately for failure or force majeure.

standard_text: Company may immediately terminate if Influencer commits or is accused of criminal acts, public scandal, offensive behavior, or breaches the Agreement.
plain_english_summary: Immediate termination for misconduct or breach.

standard_text: Company shall retain perpetual internal archival use rights for Materials, and posts made during the Term may remain accessible after termination.
plain_english_summary: Posts may stay online; archival rights survive.

standard_text: Influencer represents they are over the age of majority or have guardian consent, have no criminal record, and have the right to enter into this Agreement.
plain_english_summary: Influencer warranties about eligibility and legal ability.

standard_text: Influencer warrants they have not and will not acquire followers fraudulently and will make truthful claims based on honest opinion.
plain_english_summary: No follower fraud; honest representations required.

standard_text: Influencer warrants that Influencer Content will comply with all laws, industry standards, social platform policies, and the LVMH Supplier Code of Conduct.
plain_english_summary: Content must comply with legal and code-of-conduct rules.

standard_text: Influencer shall not disclose any Company confidential information, including unreleased advertising content, compensation terms, or the relationship itself prior to public disclosure.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must keep Company information confidential.

standard_text: All press inquiries regarding Influencer's services shall be directed to Company, and Influencer shall not comment publicly without approval.
plain_english_summary: Influencer cannot speak to media without permission.

standard_text: Each party shall indemnify, defend, and hold the other harmless from third-party claims arising from breaches or gross negligence.
plain_english_summary: Mutual indemnification for breach or negligence.

standard_text: Neither party shall be liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, exemplary, or punitive damages.
plain_english_summary: No indirect or special damages allowed.

standard_text: Influencer shall not display non-company-owned brand logos or products in video content, including clothing.
plain_english_summary: No competitor brands may appear in content.

standard_text: Company shall indemnify Influencer for third-party claims arising from Company products or services, except where caused by Influencer's misconduct.
plain_english_summary: Company covers product liability claims.

standard_text: Influencer shall comply with the LVMH Supplier Code of Conduct, including diversity, equity, and inclusion expectations.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must follow DEI and supplier code.

standard_text: Business partner shall prevent direct or indirect funding of hate groups or discriminatory organizations.
plain_english_summary: Prohibits supporting hate groups.

standard_text: Business partner shall notify Company of any acts or suspicions of corruption or influence peddling and may be terminated immediately for breach.
plain_english_summary: Anti-corruption compliance required.

standard_text: Business partner must avoid conflicts of interest and disclose any potential conflict immediately.
plain_english_summary: Must avoid and report conflicts of interest.

standard_text: Influencer may not assign or transfer this Agreement without Company consent.
plain_english_summary: Influencer cannot assign contract without permission.

standard_text: Payments are subject to legal deductions. Parties are independent contractors, not employees or agents.
plain_english_summary: Clarifies contractor status and tax deductions.

standard_text: This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of California, and any enforcement action shall be brought exclusively in California courts.
plain_english_summary: California governs; California courts have jurisdiction.

standard_text: All notices shall be deemed given upon personal delivery, email during business hours, certified mail, or overnight courier to the listed addresses.
plain_english_summary: Defines how notices must be delivered.

standard_text: If any portion of this Agreement is held void or unenforceable, the remainder shall remain binding.
plain_english_summary: Invalid parts do not affect the rest.

standard_text: This Agreement contains the entire understanding between the parties and may only be modified in writing.
plain_english_summary: Agreement is entire and requires written changes.

standard_text: Company may audit Influencer's accounts and books for seven years after termination, with rights to correct discrepancies and terminate for illegal payments.
plain_english_summary: Allows Company to audit books for 7 years.

standard_text: If Content is delivered in compliance with the campaign details and creative treatment, Influencer shall not be obligated to reshoot, but must accommodate reasonable non-material edit requests.
plain_english_summary: No reshoot if the content follows the brief, but reasonable edits are required.

standard_text: Influencer warrants that, excluding Marks and materials provided by [PARTY A], the Content will be original works created specifically for the campaign, will not infringe third-party rights, will not contain prohibited content such as profanity, nudity, illicit drugs, weapons, or defamatory or disparaging material, and will reflect Influencer's honest opinion based on actual use of the product with true and accurate statements.
plain_english_summary: Content must be original, rights-cleared, safe, and truthful.

standard_text: Each party shall indemnify and hold the other harmless from third-party claims, losses, damages, settlements, costs, and expenses arising from that party's negligence or willful misconduct or breach of any representation, warranty, or provision of the Agreement; when Influencer is the indemnifying party, client is also an indemnified party.
plain_english_summary: Mutual indemnity covers breach and negligence; client is protected when Influencer is at fault.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall create and publish one (1) TikTok video as specified in the Summary, promoting [PARTY A] and the Products.
plain_english_summary: Talent must create and post one TikTok video as required.

standard_text: Company represents and warrants that Company has full power and authority to enter into this Agreement and to grant the rights granted herein.
plain_english_summary: Company confirms they have authority to sign and grant rights.

standard_text: Influencer owns all right, title, and interest in and to the Content created for the campaign, but may not use such Content for any commercial purpose, including in connection with any other marketing campaign, at any time.
plain_english_summary: Influencer owns the content but cannot reuse it commercially outside this deal.

standard_text: [PARTY A] and its client own all right, title, and interest in and to their respective names, logos, and other trademarks (Marks).
plain_english_summary: Agency and client keep ownership of their trademarks.

standard_text: Influencer grants [PARTY A]'s client the exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free right and license to reproduce, distribute, and display the Content and Influencer's name, image, likeness, voice, and social media handles contained therein for the License Periods and Licensed Uses set forth in the campaign details, in connection with the campaign.
plain_english_summary: Client gets an exclusive worldwide license to use the content and likeness for specified periods and uses.

standard_text: Client is not obligated to take down any Content published on social media platforms during the License Period in accordance with the granted licenses, but all other forms of usage must be removed after the term.
plain_english_summary: Client may keep social posts live during the license period; other uses end when the license ends.

standard_text: Influencer shall only use [PARTY A] and client Marks in connection with providing the Services as approved by them.
plain_english_summary: Influencer can only use brand marks as approved for this campaign.

standard_text: If the Licensed Uses include paid media, Influencer shall timely take all steps required to whitelist the Content on the applicable social media platforms and analytics platforms in connection with the Posts.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must cooperate with whitelisting for paid media.

standard_text: Client may use the Posts organically on its owned and operated social media channels, websites, and e-newsletters for one month, and in paid digital media, including boosting and darkposting, for two weeks, as specified in the campaign details.
plain_english_summary: Defines client's organic and paid media usage periods.

standard_text: Influencer shall not promote or endorse, whether in a paid or organic capacity, the competitor brands specified in the campaign details for the exclusivity period set forth therein.
plain_english_summary: Influencer may not work with named competitors during the exclusivity window.

standard_text: The exclusivity period runs from one day prior to Influencer's publication of the first Post through one day after Influencer's publication of the last Post.
plain_english_summary: Exclusivity applies from one day before to one day after the campaign post.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall abide by rules of fairness, honesty, integrity, respect, and inclusion, and refrain from human rights abuses or corrupt or unethical practices including discrimination, harassment, forced labor, corruption, money laundering, and uncompetitive conduct.
plain_english_summary: Talent must follow ethics, inclusion, anti-corruption and anti-abuse rules.

standard_text: [PARTY B] retains full and exclusive ownership of all Content created without using any intellectual property owned by third parties or by [PARTY A].
plain_english_summary: Talent owns all original content they create that does not contain third-party or brand IP.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall submit an invoice on the live date agreed between the parties, and [PARTY A] shall make payment within thirty (30) days of receiving the invoice.
plain_english_summary: Talent invoices on the live date and is paid within 30 days.

standard_text: Influencer represents and warrants that all Content created under this Agreement will be original, will not infringe any third-party intellectual property rights, and will not violate any applicable laws.
plain_english_summary: Influencer guarantees content is original and legal.

standard_text: Each Party represents and warrants that the execution and performance of this Agreement will not conflict with or violate any other agreement to which such Party is bound.
plain_english_summary: Both parties confirm no conflicting agreements exist.

standard_text: Influencer represents and warrants that Influencer will comply with all applicable laws, regulations, and industry guidelines, including FTC Endorsement Guides.
plain_english_summary: Influencer commits to legal and regulatory compliance.

standard_text: Influencer shall provide the services set forth in the campaign details, including producing photo and/or video content for the campaign to be posted on Influencer's social media channels, and/or attending a client-branded event as specified.
plain_english_summary: Defines the overall services Influencer must provide (content and possibly event attendance).

standard_text: Influencer shall participate in one briefing call with the creative team prior to producing Content if requested.
plain_english_summary: A pre-production briefing call may be required.

standard_text: Influencer shall submit one Creative Treatment based on the creative brief, outlining the creative concept, proposed filming backdrop, and specific products to feature.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must prepare and submit a creative treatment for approval.

standard_text: Influencer shall disseminate one TikTok Post on the specified handle including required tags, mentions, and product name in content and caption, and must include the specified campaign partner text for the entirety of the video content.
plain_english_summary: Defines the required TikTok post and mandatory tags/text.

standard_text: Influencer shall provide clean video assets without music, text overlays, or graphics to [PARTY A] within 2024 hours after the Post goes live.
plain_english_summary: Clean version of the video must be supplied within 2024 hours.

standard_text: Influencer shall provide screenshots of TikTok metrics to [PARTY A] within 2024 hours after the Post goes live.
plain_english_summary: Performance metrics screenshots must be sent within 2024 hours.

standard_text: Influencer shall post the Content according to the schedule set forth in the campaign details, and shall not publish any Content outside of the agreed-upon schedule.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must follow the agreed posting schedule and not post early or late.

standard_text: Influencer shall be paid a fee of [AMOUNT], due no later than sixty (60) days after the last day of the month in which the last Post is published by Influencer or, if no Posts are to be published, the month in which the last Influencer materials are delivered.
plain_english_summary: Defines the total fee and timing of payment after campaign completion.

standard_text: Payment of the Fee is conditioned on Influencer completing all Services as set forth in the Agreement and not being in uncured material breach, if capable of cure.
plain_english_summary: Payment is only due if the Influencer completes services and is not in material breach.

standard_text: Influencer is solely responsible for all taxes, withholdings, and other statutory or contractual obligations related to the Fee, and [PARTY A] shall not provide any benefits such as social security, workers' compensation, disability, health, or unemployment insurance.
plain_english_summary: Influencer handles their own taxes and benefits; the agency does not.

standard_text: Posts shall remain on Influencer's social channels for no less than one (1) year, unless directed by [PARTY A] to remove them earlier.
plain_english_summary: Content must stay live for at least a year unless asked to remove it.

standard_text: Influencer shall validate social media accounts in the analytics platform used by [PARTY A] so metrics can be retrieved and shared with the client on a read-only basis.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must connect their accounts to the analytics platform.

standard_text: If [PARTY B] fails to perform the Services required under the Agreement for reasons not caused by an Event of Force Majeure, [PARTY A] shall owe no compensation.
plain_english_summary: Talent forfeits payment if they fail to perform without a valid force majeure event.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall not misrepresent the source of anything in the Content, including impersonating another individual or entity.
plain_english_summary: Talent may not impersonate others or misrepresent content sources.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall clearly and conspicuously disclose [PARTY B]'s affiliation with [PARTY A] in all sponsored posts in compliance with FTC endorsement guidelines.
plain_english_summary: Talent must follow FTC disclosure rules for all sponsored content.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall incorporate appropriate disclosures in each Post and immediately inform [PARTY A] of any changes in [PARTY B]'s opinions or findings related to the Content.
plain_english_summary: Talent must disclose sponsorship and notify the brand if their views change.

standard_text: [PARTY A] shall provide a creative brief setting forth campaign requirements, and the parties shall finalize a mutually approved creative treatment, which [PARTY A] will review and approve per the agreed schedule.
plain_english_summary: Creative execution must follow an approved brief and treatment.

standard_text: If Content is not delivered in compliance with the campaign details and creative treatment, Influencer may be required to reshoot, and failure to reshoot and deliver compliant Content within the time required entitles [PARTY A] to terminate the Agreement.
plain_english_summary: If the content does not meet the brief and isn't fixed, the agency can terminate.

standard_text: Influencer shall remove Posts from Influencer's social channels within twenty-four (24) hours of notice from [PARTY A] in the event of Influencer's uncured material breach or as reasonably requested in good faith due to unforeseen changes in circumstances, including changes in law.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must be able to take posts down within 24 hours when requested in certain circumstances.

standard_text: Influencer is responsible for obtaining all necessary licenses and releases for third-party materials and appearances in the Content (excluding client Marks or materials provided by [PARTY A]) and shall provide copies on request.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must clear third-party rights and provide releases if asked.

standard_text: [PARTY A] may terminate the Agreement in whole or in part at any time for convenience upon written notice, paying Influencer the portion of the Fee due for Services actually completed in accordance with the campaign details and creative treatment.
plain_english_summary: [PARTY A] can terminate for convenience and pay only for completed work.

standard_text: [PARTY A] may terminate the Agreement upon Influencer's material breach, which, if capable of cure in [PARTY A]'s reasonable opinion, is not cured within five (5) days after notice.
plain_english_summary: Agency can terminate for material breach not cured within 5 days.

standard_text: [PARTY A] may terminate the Agreement if Influencer delivers noncompliant Content after two opportunities to reshoot; in such case [PARTY A] shall pay only the portion of the Fee due for Services actually completed in accordance with the campaign details and creative treatment.
plain_english_summary: If after two reshoots the content still fails, agency can end the deal and pay only for compliant work.

standard_text: Upon termination for material breach, no Fee shall be paid to Influencer.
plain_english_summary: If terminated for Influencer's breach, they may lose their fee.

standard_text: Influencer represents and warrants that Influencer has the right and authority to enter into the Agreement, perform obligations, and grant the rights set forth, and that doing so will not breach any other agreement.
plain_english_summary: Influencer promises they are legally allowed to sign and perform this deal.

standard_text: Influencer warrants that the Services will be performed in compliance with all applicable laws and regulations and with the endorsement and disclosure guidelines in Attachment 1.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must follow laws and the detailed FTC-style disclosure rules.

standard_text: Influencer shall not make statements or commit acts that, in [PARTY A]'s reasonable opinion, make Influencer the subject of public disrepute, contempt, or scandal affecting the reputations of Influencer, [PARTY A], or client, nor may Influencer defame or disparage them or their products or services.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must avoid conduct or statements that create scandal or disparage the brand or agency.

standard_text: Influencer shall comply with the endorsement and disclosure guidelines, including clearly disclosing that Influencer received payment or value in each post in a way that is difficult to miss and easily understandable.
plain_english_summary: Every sponsored post must contain clear, prominent disclosure of the paid relationship.

standard_text: For static social content with captions, disclosure must appear before any truncation such as "show more" and cannot be buried within a long list of hashtags; acceptable disclosures include terms such as "ad", "#ad", "sponsored", or "#CompanyPartner".
plain_english_summary: Placement and format of disclosures in captions are strictly controlled.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall not disparage or denigrate [PARTY A], [PARTY A]'s brands, or products.
plain_english_summary: Talent must avoid negative statements about the brand.

standard_text: [PARTY A] warrants that it will comply with all applicable laws, regulations, and court orders in connection with its products and content distribution.
plain_english_summary: Brand agrees to follow all relevant laws.

standard_text: Upon execution of this Agreement, [PARTY_NAME] agrees to pay Contractor a non-refundable retainer fee of [AMOUNT] [CURRENCY] (the "Retainer"). The Retainer shall be credited toward the total project fee of [AMOUNT] [CURRENCY] (the "Total Fee") and is earned upon receipt. The remaining balance of [AMOUNT] [CURRENCY] shall be invoiced in accordance with the following schedule: [PAYMENT_SCHEDULE]. All invoices for remaining amounts shall be submitted upon completion of deliverables as outlined in Exhibit A (Scope of Work), with payment due within [NET_DAYS] days of invoice receipt. The Retainer secures Contractor's availability and commitment to the project timeline and compensates Contractor for initial planning, research, and project setup activities. In the event [PARTY_NAME] terminates this Agreement prior to completion without cause, the Retainer shall be retained by Contractor as liquidated damages, and Client shall remain obligated to pay for any completed work beyond the Retainer amount on a pro-rata basis. If Contractor terminates without cause or fails to perform, the Retainer shall be refunded on a pro-rata basis less the value of work completed. All payments are subject to receipt of proper tax documentation and are inclusive of all applicable taxes, fees, and charges except as otherwise specified herein.

standard_text: Influencer may not rely solely on built-in platform disclosure tools and must include disclosures within the content itself.

plain_english_summary: Influencer must genuinely use the product and avoid unsubstantiated or misleading claims.

standard_text: Each party shall indemnify and hold the other harmless from all third-party damages arising from its own acts, omissions, or breach of any representation, warranty, or covenant under the Agreement.
plain_english_summary: Mutual indemnity for breach and wrongful acts.

standard_text: Influencer represents and warrants that Influencer has not acquired followers fraudulently and all engagement metrics are genuine.
plain_english_summary: Influencer confirms authentic follower base.

standard_text: Company represents and warrants that the Products are safe for use as intended and comply with all applicable product safety regulations.
plain_english_summary: Company confirms product safety compliance.

standard_text: The total fee for all Services rendered under this Agreement shall be [AMOUNT] [CURRENCY] (the "Fixed Fee"), payable in accordance with the payment terms specified in Section [SECTION_REF]. The Fixed Fee is a firm, all-inclusive price and includes compensation for all services, deliverables, rights granted, licenses, revisions (up to [NUMBER] rounds of revisions as specified in the Scope of Work), labor, materials, and overhead associated with completion of the Services. Unless expressly stated otherwise in Exhibit A (Inclusions and Exclusions), the Fixed Fee specifically includes: (i) all project management and coordination activities; (ii) all research, planning, and strategy development; (iii) all meetings, calls, and communications reasonably necessary for project completion; and (iv) all standard tools, software licenses, and materials required for Service delivery. The Fixed Fee specifically excludes and shall be subject to additional charges: (i) revisions beyond the [NUMBER] rounds included herein, charged at [AMOUNT] [CURRENCY] per additional revision or on a time-and-materials basis; (ii) services outside the Scope of Work as defined in Exhibit A; (iii) third-party costs including stock photography, premium fonts, paid advertising, or other media buys; (iv) travel expenses unless pre-approved in writing; and (v) rush fees for expedited delivery timelines. Any changes to the Scope of Work that would reasonably be expected to require additional time or resources shall be subject to a written change order and additional fees as mutually agreed by the parties in writing prior to commencement of such additional work.

In no event shall total compensation under this Agreement, including Base Fee and all bonuses, exceed [AMOUNT] [CURRENCY] without a written amendment to this Agreement. standard_text: A Force Majeure Event is any event or circumstance not caused by the affected party that prevents it from complying with obligations; during such an event, the nonperforming party is excused if it uses reasonable efforts, protected itself where reasonable, and complies with its notice obligations.
plain_english_summary: Defines force majeure and when a party is excused from performance.

standard_text: Upon occurrence of a Force Majeure Event, the nonperforming party shall promptly notify the other of its effect and expected duration, update that information as needed, and use reasonable efforts to limit damages and resume performance.
plain_english_summary: Force majeure requires prompt notice and efforts to mitigate and resume.

standard_text: Influencer shall keep confidential all non-public business, technical, financial, and campaign information about [PARTY A] and client, including the terms of the Agreement, and shall not disclose or use such Confidential Information except to perform the Services.

standard_text: In the event of a breach of the Agreement by [PARTY A], Influencer's sole remedy shall be monetary damages and Influencer shall have no right to seek injunctive relief.
plain_english_summary: Influencer cannot seek injunctions, only money damages.

standard_text: A breach of the Agreement may cause [PARTY A] or client irreparable harm, and they may seek injunctive relief without posting a bond.

standard_text: Each party is an independent contractor and not a partner, joint venturer, or agent of the other and shall not bind the other to any contract; Influencer is solely responsible for all statutory and contractual obligations arising from the relationship.

standard_text: Either party shall have the right to terminate this Agreement at any time and for any reason, effective upon [NOTICE_DAYS] days prior written notice to the other party. Written notice must be delivered by email to the address specified in this Agreement, with a copy sent via certified mail, return receipt requested, or nationally recognized courier service. Upon receipt of such notice, the parties shall work in good faith to transition any ongoing work and settle all outstanding obligations. Notwithstanding the foregoing, all payments due for services rendered or deliverables completed prior to the effective date of termination shall become immediately due and payable within [PAYMENT_DAYS] days of termination. [PARTY_NAME] shall promptly return or destroy, at the other party's election, all Confidential Information, documents, materials, and work product in their possession or control within [RETURN_DAYS] business days of termination. The following provisions shall survive termination of this Agreement: confidentiality obligations, payment obligations for work completed, indemnification, limitation of liability, and governing law provisions. Neither party shall be liable to the other for any damages arising solely from termination in accordance with this provision, provided that termination shall not relieve either party of obligations incurred prior to the effective date of termination.

standard_text: Neither party shall be liable for failure to perform its obligations under this Agreement if such failure is caused by circumstances beyond its reasonable control, including but not limited to acts of God, natural disasters, war, terrorism, civil unrest, government actions or restrictions, epidemics, pandemics, public health emergencies, labor disputes, strikes, supply chain disruptions, telecommunications failures, power outages, or any other event that could not have been prevented by reasonable precautions (each a "Force Majeure Event"). Upon occurrence of a Force Majeure Event, the affected party shall promptly notify the other party in writing, describing the event and its expected duration, and shall use commercially reasonable efforts to mitigate the effects of the Force Majeure Event and resume performance as soon as reasonably practicable. Performance obligations shall be suspended for the duration of the Force Majeure Event. If a Force Majeure Event continues for more than [SUSPENSION_DAYS] consecutive days, either party may terminate this Agreement upon [TERMINATION_NOTICE_DAYS] days written notice to the other party. Upon such termination, [PARTY_NAME] shall pay for all services satisfactorily performed and deliverables accepted prior to the Force Majeure Event, and neither party shall be liable to the other for any damages arising from such termination. Notwithstanding the foregoing, Force Majeure shall not excuse payment obligations for work completed prior to the Force Majeure Event.

standard_text: Each party (as "Disclosing Party") may disclose to the other party (as "Receiving Party") certain confidential and proprietary information in connection with this Agreement. "Confidential Information" means all non-public information disclosed by either party, whether orally, in writing, or by inspection of tangible objects, including without limitation business plans, technical data, customer information, financial information, product designs, software code, trade secrets, and any information marked as confidential or that reasonably should be understood to be confidential given the nature of the information and circumstances of disclosure. Each party agrees to: (a) maintain Confidential Information in strict confidence; (b) not disclose Confidential Information to third parties without prior written consent; (c) use Confidential Information solely for purposes of this Agreement; (d) protect Confidential Information with at least the same degree of care used to protect its own confidential information, but no less than reasonable care; and (e) limit internal disclosure to personnel with a legitimate need to know who are bound by confidentiality obligations. Confidential Information shall not include information that: (i) is or becomes publicly available through no breach of this Agreement; (ii) was rightfully known prior to disclosure; (iii) is rightfully obtained from third parties without confidentiality restrictions; or (iv) is independently developed without use of Confidential Information. These obligations shall survive termination for [YEARS] years. Each party acknowledges that breach of confidentiality may cause irreparable harm for which monetary damages are inadequate, and agrees that the non-breaching party shall be entitled to seek equitable relief, including injunction and specific performance, without posting bond.

Notwithstanding [BRAND_NAME]'s approval rights, [BRAND_NAME] acknowledges that [CREATOR_NAME] is an independent contractor with a unique voice, style, and creative perspective that are integral to the value of this partnership. [BRAND_NAME] agrees to exercise its approval rights reasonably and in good faith, and shall not unreasonably withhold approval for content that aligns with the creative brief, complies with brand guidelines, and meets professional quality standards. If [BRAND_NAME] fails to respond within the specified review period, [CREATOR_NAME] may send a follow-up notice, and if no response is received within an additional [GRACE_PERIOD_DAYS] business days, the content shall be deemed approved and [CREATOR_NAME] may proceed with publication.

standard_text: Notwithstanding [BRAND_NAME]'s approval rights as specified in this Agreement, [CREATOR_NAME] shall retain primary creative control over the style, tone, format, and presentation of all Deliverables, subject to compliance with the creative brief, brand guidelines, and legal requirements. The parties acknowledge that [CREATOR_NAME] has been engaged for this project specifically because of [CREATOR_NAME]'s unique creative voice, authentic relationship with their audience, and demonstrated expertise in content creation, and that excessive brand control over creative elements may diminish the effectiveness and authenticity of the content. Accordingly, the parties agree to the following principles: (i) [CREATOR_NAME] shall have discretion over creative elements including filming style, editing choices, music selection, personal storytelling approach, and other artistic decisions that reflect [CREATOR_NAME]'s authentic voice, provided such elements do not contradict brand guidelines or misrepresent [BRAND_NAME]'s products or services; (ii) [BRAND_NAME] may provide creative direction, preferences, and feedback, but shall not mandate specific scripting, rigid talking points, or overly prescriptive requirements that would make the content appear inauthentic or inconsistent with [CREATOR_NAME]'s typical content style; (iii) [CREATOR_NAME] retains the right to integrate [BRAND_NAME]'s messaging and products into content in a manner that feels organic and natural to [CREATOR_NAME]'s audience; (iv) [BRAND_NAME] may reject content that materially deviates from the agreed-upon creative brief, contains factual inaccuracies, misrepresents products, violates brand guidelines, or includes inappropriate or offensive material, but shall not reject content solely due to subjective creative preferences unrelated to brand integrity; and (v) in the event of creative disputes, both parties agree to engage in good faith discussions to reach a mutually acceptable solution that respects both [BRAND_NAME]'s legitimate business interests and [CREATOR_NAME]'s creative autonomy. [CREATOR_NAME] acknowledges that creative control does not supersede [BRAND_NAME]'s approval rights with respect to brand accuracy, legal compliance, and adherence to the scope of work.

standard_text: [CREATOR_NAME] acknowledges that this Agreement creates a material connection between [CREATOR_NAME] and [BRAND_NAME] as defined by the Federal Trade Commission (FTC), and that any endorsement, testimonial, review, or mention of [BRAND_NAME]'s products or services by [CREATOR_NAME] must be accompanied by clear and conspicuous disclosure of this relationship. [CREATOR_NAME] represents and warrants that any opinions, claims, or statements made about [BRAND_NAME]'s products or services shall reflect [CREATOR_NAME]'s honest and genuine views and experiences, and shall not contain any false, misleading, or deceptive information. standard_text: The parties acknowledge and agree to maintain the confidentiality of all proprietary and confidential information disclosed during the term of this Agreement, subject to the following standard industry exceptions. Confidential Information shall not include information that: (a) is or becomes generally available to the public through no act or omission of the Receiving Party; (b) was in the Receiving Party's lawful possession prior to disclosure by the Disclosing Party, as evidenced by written records; (c) is lawfully disclosed to the Receiving Party by a third party who has no confidentiality obligations with respect to such information; (d) is independently developed by the Receiving Party without reference to or use of the Disclosing Party's Confidential Information, as evidenced by contemporaneous written records; or (e) is approved for release by written authorization of the Disclosing Party. Additionally, the Receiving Party may disclose Confidential Information to the extent required by applicable law, regulation, or valid court order, provided that the Receiving Party: (i) provides the Disclosing Party with prompt written notice of such requirement prior to disclosure; (ii) cooperates with the Disclosing Party in seeking a protective order or other appropriate relief; and (iii) discloses only that portion of Confidential Information which is legally required to be disclosed. The Receiving Party may disclose Confidential Information to its employees, contractors, consultants, advisors, and legal counsel who have a legitimate business need to know and who are bound by professional obligations of confidentiality or written agreements providing protections substantially similar to those set forth herein. The confidentiality obligations shall remain in effect for [YEARS] years following termination of this Agreement.

standard_text: Each party (as "Indemnifying Party") shall defend, indemnify, and hold harmless the other party (as "Indemnified Party") and its officers, directors, employees, and agents from and against any third-party claims, demands, losses, damages, liabilities, costs, and expenses (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising from: (a) the Indemnifying Party's breach of its representations, warranties, or material obligations under this Agreement; (b) the Indemnifying Party's negligence or willful misconduct in performance of this Agreement; (c) claims that the Indemnifying Party's deliverables, services, or materials infringe or misappropriate any third-party intellectual property rights; (d) the Indemnifying Party's violation of applicable laws or regulations; or (e) bodily injury or property damage caused by the Indemnifying Party's acts or omissions. The Indemnifying Party shall have the right to control the defense of any indemnified claim using counsel reasonably acceptable to the Indemnified Party, provided that the Indemnified Party may participate in the defense with its own counsel at its own expense. The Indemnifying Party shall not settle any claim without the Indemnified Party's prior written consent if such settlement would impose any obligations or liability on the Indemnified Party. The Indemnified Party shall: (i) promptly notify the Indemnifying Party in writing of any claim; (ii) reasonably cooperate in the defense of the claim; and (iii) not settle or compromise the claim without the Indemnifying Party's prior written consent. These mutual indemnification obligations are independent of and in addition to any other rights or remedies available at law or in equity.

standard_text: [PARTY_NAME] may terminate this Agreement immediately upon written notice to the other party in the event of a material breach of this Agreement, provided that the breaching party fails to cure such breach within [CURE_DAYS] days after receiving written notice specifying the nature of the breach in reasonable detail. Upon termination for cause, the non-breaching party shall be entitled to pursue all available remedies at law or in equity, including but not limited to recovery of damages, specific performance, and attorney fees and costs. The terminating party shall have no obligation to make further payments for work performed after the effective date of termination.
