standard_text: [PARTY A] shall not disparage or denigrate [PARTY B] or [PARTY B]'s reputation.
plain_english_summary: Brand agrees not to disparage the talent.

standard_text: [PARTY A] shall indemnify [PARTY B] for damages arising from the use of any materials or products supplied by [PARTY A], including product liability claims.
plain_english_summary: Brand covers the talent for issues arising from brand-supplied materials or products.

standard_text: The indemnified party shall give prompt notice of any indemnifiable claim, and the indemnifying party may participate in the defense at its own expense.
plain_english_summary: Indemnifying party has the right to participate in defense after notice.

standard_text: [PARTY B]'s indemnification obligations shall not exceed the total compensation paid to [PARTY B] under this Agreement.
plain_english_summary: Talent's indemnity exposure is capped at total compensation.

standard_text: An Event of Force Majeure includes natural catastrophes, labor disputes or strikes, acts of God or public enemy, war, delays of common carriers, disease, epidemic, outbreak, municipal ordinances, state or federal laws, governmental orders or regulations, or any similar cause beyond [PARTY B]'s control that adversely affects [PARTY B]'s Services or [PARTY A]'s rights to use the Content.
plain_english_summary: Defines force majeure events that excuse performance.

standard_text: If a Force Majeure Event lasts more than fifteen (15) days, [PARTY A] may terminate the Agreement and shall owe only the pro rata portion of compensation earned up to the date of termination.
plain_english_summary: If force majeure continues, brand may terminate and pay only pro rata compensation.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall only be entitled to compensation accrued up to the date of termination if the Agreement ends due to disability or Force Majeure.
plain_english_summary: Talent only receives earned compensation if terminated due to disability or force majeure.

standard_text: Confidential Information means any non-public information that [PARTY A] does not designate for public dissemination, including advertising materials, unreleased products, the terms of the Agreement, and the compensation paid to [PARTY B].
plain_english_summary: Defines what counts as confidential information.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall not disclose or use Confidential Information for [PARTY B]'s own benefit or any third party's benefit without [PARTY A]'s express written consent.
plain_english_summary: Talent may not share or use confidential information except to perform services.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall only use Confidential Information as required to perform obligations under the Agreement.
plain_english_summary: Confidential information may only be used for contract performance.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall protect Confidential Information from unauthorized use or disclosure and take all necessary actions to prevent or remedy any breach of confidentiality.
plain_english_summary: Talent must safeguard confidential information and prevent breaches.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall not remove or destroy proprietary or confidential legends or markings on Confidential Information.
plain_english_summary: Talent must keep confidentiality markings intact.

standard_text: [PARTY B] shall not develop any products or services containing concepts or ideas derived from [PARTY A]'s Confidential Information.
plain_english_summary: Talent may not use confidential ideas to develop other content or products.

standard_text: All notices required or permitted under this Agreement shall be in writing and shall be deemed given when delivered personally, sent by email, or sent by certified mail to the addresses set forth herein.
plain_english_summary: Defines how formal notices must be delivered.

standard_text: Notices sent by email shall be deemed effective upon transmission if sent during normal business hours, or on the next business day if sent outside business hours.
plain_english_summary: Email notices are effective when sent during business hours.

standard_text: Either Party may change its notice address by providing written notice to the other Party in accordance with this Section.
plain_english_summary: Parties can update their contact addresses with notice.

standard_text: If Influencer utilizes any persons who are members of any union that would have jurisdiction over content created hereunder, Influencer shall notify Company prior to content creation.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must disclose union membership before creating content.

standard_text: Influencer shall promptly notify Company of any third-party claims, legal proceedings, or regulatory inquiries related to the Content or this Agreement.
plain_english_summary: Influencer must report any legal issues promptly.

standard_text: The limitations of liability set forth herein shall not apply to breaches of confidentiality, indemnification obligations, or damages arising from gross negligence or willful misconduct.
plain_english_summary: Liability caps don't apply to serious breaches or misconduct.

standard_text: This Agreement may be executed in counterparts, each of which shall be deemed an original, and all of which together shall constitute one and the same instrument.
plain_english_summary: Contract can be signed in multiple copies.

standard_text: Electronic signatures and PDF copies shall be deemed original signatures for all purposes of this Agreement.
plain_english_summary: Electronic and PDF signatures are valid.

standard_text: No waiver of any provision of this Agreement shall be effective unless in writing and signed by the waiving Party.
plain_english_summary: Waivers must be written and signed to be valid.

standard_text: The failure of either Party to enforce any provision of this Agreement shall not constitute a waiver of that Party's right to enforce such provision in the future.
plain_english_summary: Not enforcing a term doesn't waive future enforcement rights.

standard_text: This Agreement may not be amended or modified except by a written instrument signed by both Parties.
plain_english_summary: Changes require written agreement from both parties.

standard_text: Any amendment to this Agreement shall be attached hereto and incorporated by reference.
plain_english_summary: Amendments become part of the original agreement.

standard_text: Influencer shall not license, sell, or otherwise transfer any Content created under this Agreement to any third party without Company's prior written consent.
plain_english_summary: Influencer cannot sell or license the content to others.

standard_text: During the Term, Influencer shall post Content exclusively on the platforms specified in this Agreement and shall not cross-post to other platforms without Company's approval.
